{{italic title}}
'''''Raw Food Made Easy for 1 or 2 People''''' is a 2005 recipe book by raw food chef [[Jennifer Cornbleet]].  The best-selling book<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bookpubco.com/catalog/titles/best-sellers?page=1|title=Catalog - Healthy Living Publications • Books Alive • Sproutman • Norman Walker|publisher=}}</ref> promotes the [[raw foodism|raw food diet]]—a dietary movement that encourages the consumption of uncooked foods—to obtain maximum health benefits.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vegcooking.com/chef_jennifer_cornbleet.asp|title=Vegan Food PETA|publisher=}}</ref>

The book features 115 recipes, including 21 breakfast recipes, 64 lunch and dinner recipes and 30 dessert recipes.  Each recipe yields servings for one or two people.  All the recipes in this book are [[Raw veganism|vegan]], and exclude the use of meat, poultry, fish, and dairy products, focusing entirely on fruits, vegetables, and nuts and seeds.

The book was published in August 2005 by the Book Publishing Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bookpubco.com/|title=Book Publishing Co. - Healthy Living Publications • Books Alive • Sproutman • Norman Walker|date=2 February 2002|publisher=}}</ref>

==Bibliography==
*Jennifer Cornbleet, ''Raw Food Made Easy for 1 or 2 People''.  Summertown, Tennessee: Book Publishing Company, 2005.  {{ISBN|978-1-57067-175-3}}.

