{{About|the 2006 company|the 2015 ticketing search engine|TickX}}
{{Multiple issues|
{{primary sources|date=December 2009}}
{{orphan|date=February 2009}}
}}

'''Tickex.com''' was a [[United States]] and [[UK]] based [[search engine]] dedicated to live event tickets; [[concerts]], [[sports]], and [[theatre]]. The business did not sell tickets directly to consumers, instead the search engine [[Search aggregator|aggregated]]  and displayed tickets from other sites then redirected the user to the chosen site for purchase. Tickex listed ticket vendors in both the primary and secondary ticket markets including companies  [[Ticketmaster]], [[Stubhub]], [[Ticketsnow]], [[EBAY]], [[Viagogo]], and [[Tickets.com]] providing customers the ability to search, compare, and buy tickets based on price, location, and date.<ref>http://www.ticketnews.com/TickEx-Finds-the-Tickets-You-Want27127.</ref>

In addition to the Tickex.com search engine the company maintained several other mediums for customers to access their inventory. Tickex provided [[desktop widgets]] which can be placed on any [[webpage]] and provides visitors of other sites access to the Tickex catalogue of tickets.<ref>[http://mashable.com/2007/08/21/tickex/ TickEx Launches Ticket Search in the U.S<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

In November 2007 Tickex "announced the launch of its GIG*gle application (now re-branded as the Tickex application), which allowed [[Facebook]] users to search for live events, such as [[sports]] games, live [[theatre]] and [[concerts]] in the [[United States|US]] or [[UK]]." The application also allowed users to see what tickets are available and see who among their friends are interested in attending.<ref>[http://www.901am.com/2007/tickex-launches-giggle-ticket-search-application-for-the-facebook-platform.html TickEx launches GIG*gle Ticket Search Application for the Facebook Platform | 901am<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

The company was founded in 2006 by [[University of San Francisco]] graduate Daniel Brinderson.<ref>[http://www.ticketsummit.org/2007/speakers.htm Ticket Summit 2007 Speakers<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The privately held company is backed by a [[Southern California]] based private investor and raised $1.5 million in its initial round of investment.<ref>[http://www.americanventure.tv/index.php?seccion=ver&id=149. TickEx completed $1.5 million funding - November 9th, 2007 | America Venture TV<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

Tickex operated solely in the [[UK]] before expanding operations to the [[United States|US]] in the fall of 2006.<ref>[https://venturebeat.com/2007/08/21/tickex-offering-best-priced-event-tickets-comes-to-the-us/ TickEx, offering best-priced event tickets, comes to the U.S. » VentureBeat<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

